@startuml Slot 6: Middleware Federation Architecture
!theme plain

title Middleware Federation Service — RDI to GitLab to Search Hub

skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor<<rdi>> #FEF3C7
  BackgroundColor<<middleware>> #D1FAE5
  BackgroundColor<<storage>> #DBEAFE
  BackgroundColor<<planned>> #E9D5FF
  BackgroundColor<<hub>> #FCE7F3
  BorderColor #666
}

package "Research Data Infrastructures" <<rdi>> {
  [E!DAL-PGP\nSchema.org JSON-LD] as EDAL
  [Bonares Repository\nINSPIRE XML] as BONARES
  [EDAPHOBASE\nSQL Database] as EDAPHO
  [OpenAGRAR\nSchema.org JSON-LD] as OPENAGRAR
}

package "Middleware Federation Service" <<middleware>> {
  [Harvest Adapter\n(OAI-PMH / REST / SQL)] as HARVEST
  [Format Detector\n(Schema.org / INSPIRE\n/ CSV / SQL)] as DETECT
  [Format Plugins\n(schema_org, inspire,\ndarwin_core_csv,\nsql_reader)] as PLUGINS
  [ARC Builder\n(create RO-Crate)] as BUILDER
  [Pivot Registry\n(Agrischemas profiles\n- aspirational)] as PIVOT
}

package "Storage Layer" <<storage>> {
  [GitLab DataHub\nARC repository] as GITLAB
}

package "[Planned] OAI-PMH Service" <<planned>> {
  [OAI-PMH 2.0 Endpoint\nreads ARC from GitLab] as OAI
}

package "FAIRagro Search Hub" <<hub>> {
  [Search Index\n& API] as SEARCH
}

' RDI connections
EDAL --> HARVEST : Schema.org JSON-LD
BONARES --> HARVEST : INSPIRE XML
EDAPHO --> HARVEST : SQL query
OPENAGRAR --> HARVEST : Schema.org JSON-LD

' Middleware internal flow
HARVEST --> DETECT : raw metadata
DETECT --> PLUGINS : detected format
PLUGINS --> BUILDER : flat dict
BUILDER --> PIVOT : model entities
BUILDER --> GITLAB : push ARC RO-Crate

' Planned OAI-PMH Service
GITLAB --> OAI : ARC metadata

' Search Hub harvests via OAI-PMH
OAI --> SEARCH : OAI-PMH 2.0\nharvest protocol

note right of OAI
  Planned service (separate).
  Not part of FAIRweaver.
  Reads ARCs from GitLab,
  serves OAI-PMH 2.0 records.
end note

note right of SEARCH
  Search Hub harvests via OAI-PMH.
  No direct GitLab access.
end note

note bottom of PIVOT
  Agrischemas is aspirational:
  in development, not yet adopted
  by RDIs. Used as internal
  entity model within ARCs.
end note

@enduml
